CatDescriptText: Mrs. Virginia Davis, hotel worker, 510 Armandale Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 9, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that we are spending too much money for foreign aid? Do you think that what we have spent has halted the spread of communism?" answer reads: "I do, and the main reason is that people who were born in this country are in dire need of help.  This holds true for teh South as well as the North."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Virginia Davis wearing a tweed coat, holding a dark handbag on left arm, standing on Wood Street in front of Equitable Gas Company, Downtown
